♪In the deep red windows lies mundane dust♪

12
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:40,980
=Are You The One=

13
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,980
=Episode 11=

14
00:01:51,910 --> 00:01:53,670
You wanted to inscribe for the shop.

15
00:01:53,670 --> 00:01:54,660
Have you decided

16
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:55,840
what to write?

17
00:01:57,440 --> 00:01:58,280
Not yet.

18
00:01:58,830 --> 00:02:00,300
Do you have any suggestions for me?

19
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:02,970
You can think later.

20
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:05,910
I feel

21
00:02:05,910 --> 00:02:07,660
that in these days of rest at home,

22
00:02:07,800 --> 00:02:08,730
you've changed a lot.

23
00:02:10,150 --> 00:02:10,990
Changed?

24
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:14,500
Not only do you help with chores
and ease my worries,

25
00:02:15,110 --> 00:02:16,180
but you're more thoughtful.

26
00:02:28,870 --> 00:02:29,710
Miantang,

27
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,180
you're really here.

28
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,160
Dear.

29
00:02:33,640 --> 00:02:34,620
I finally found you.

30
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,290
Sir,

31
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,640
are you mistaken?

32
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:40,270
- I'm not your wife.
- I'm not mistaken.

33
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:41,110
It's me.

34
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,550
Miantang, I'm your husband.

35
00:02:42,550 --> 00:02:43,390
I'm Cui Jiu.

36
00:02:46,150 --> 00:02:46,990
Who is this fool?

37
00:02:46,990 --> 00:02:48,060
Spouting nonsense.

38
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:51,520
Honey, did you offend someone outside,

39
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:53,010
causing them to ruin my reputation?

40
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,240
No. He's not your husband.

41
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,250
Your husband is here.

42
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:57,640
I am your husband.

43
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:59,250
He is just an impostor.

44
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:01,500
How can you prove you're not an impostor?

45
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:02,800
I...

46
00:03:04,270 --> 00:03:05,150
Have you forgotten?

47
00:03:05,150 --> 00:03:06,010
Three years ago,

48
00:03:06,150 --> 00:03:07,240
on June 7th,

49
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:08,830
you traveled from Beizhou to the capital

50
00:03:08,830 --> 00:03:09,810
encountered bandits,

51
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:10,920
and disappeared.

52
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:11,760
Right?

53
00:03:12,550 --> 00:03:14,100
- Bandits...
- In these three years,

54
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:16,430
I sent people to search for you everywhere.

55
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:18,310
Finally, Heaven didn't disappoint me.

56
00:03:18,310 --> 00:03:20,410
I heard the news about you in Lingquan Town.

57
00:03:20,590 --> 00:03:22,340
So I rushed over from the capital.

58
00:03:22,830 --> 00:03:24,430
If I weren't the real Cui Jiu,

59
00:03:24,430 --> 00:03:25,730
who else would know this?

60
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:27,780
This impostor.

61
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:29,180
Why don't you say anything?

62
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:30,290
Are you feeling guilty?

63
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,200
Honey,

64
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:33,990
if you don't speak,

65
00:03:33,990 --> 00:03:35,010
I might believe it.

66
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:36,750
He came all the way

67
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:37,780
from the capital.

68
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,100
What you said

69
00:03:41,670 --> 00:03:42,730
is what I wanted to ask.

70
00:03:43,390 --> 00:03:44,230
You said

71
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:47,060
you came specially from the capital?

72
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,270
Exactly.

73
00:03:48,270 --> 00:03:49,620
Then I need to ask.

74
00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:52,340
The fabric of your clothes

75
00:03:52,670 --> 00:03:54,430
is from Jianlin

76
00:03:54,430 --> 00:03:56,060
and you speak with a Jianlin accent.

77
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:58,290
The Cui family has been

78
00:03:58,550 --> 00:04:00,570
genuine capital folks for three generations.

79
00:04:01,670 --> 00:04:02,520
I...

80
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:04,520
Did you make a detour

81
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:05,660
to come here?

82
00:04:06,550 --> 00:04:09,010
My wet nurse is from Jianlin.

83
00:04:09,060 --> 00:04:11,060
She made me these clothes

84
00:04:11,060 --> 00:04:13,060
and taught me about the accent.

85
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:13,980
What's the problem?

86
00:04:14,780 --> 00:04:16,140
Words full of deceit.

87
00:04:16,660 --> 00:04:19,140
You're taking advantage
of my wife's memory loss

88
00:04:19,140 --> 00:04:20,660
and causing confusion here.

89
00:04:20,660 --> 00:04:21,500
I advise you

90
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:23,620
to give up on this matter.

91
00:04:27,580 --> 00:04:28,580
I went

92
00:04:29,780 --> 00:04:31,100
to my wife's house several times

93
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:32,300
to propose,

94
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:34,740
so my father-in-law

95
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:36,900
finally agreed.

96
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:40,420
You're the one with deceitful words.

97
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:41,780
I can also claim

98
00:04:41,780 --> 00:04:43,460
that I went to Beizhou myself

99
00:04:43,460 --> 00:04:45,380
and personally asked her father for marriage.

100
00:04:45,580 --> 00:04:46,940
You're eloquent,

101
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:47,980
but you don't know

102
00:04:47,980 --> 00:04:49,860
my father has long passed away.

103
00:04:51,380 --> 00:04:53,260
My husband just tested you,

104
00:04:53,420 --> 00:04:54,660
and your lies are exposed.

105
00:04:55,060 --> 00:04:55,900
Moru,

106
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:57,540
send this fraud to the authorities.

107
00:04:57,780 --> 00:04:59,020
- Yes.
- No, no.

108
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:00,140
Wait.

109
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:01,660
You can deny me,

110
00:05:01,660 --> 00:05:02,860
but you cannot deny this.

111
00:05:12,780 --> 00:05:14,060
This is our marriage certificate

112
00:05:14,060 --> 00:05:15,140
in black and white.

113
00:05:15,340 --> 00:05:16,660
(Beizhou)
With the official seal.

114
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:18,380
Now I want to see

115
00:05:18,380 --> 00:05:20,540
who dares to say I'm not Cui Jiu.

116
00:05:21,140 --> 00:05:21,980
This is impossible.

117
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:26,860
Liu Miantang brought this

118
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:28,100
with her to Mount Yang.

119
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:30,100
It has now come in handy.

120
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:33,860
She's always been scheming,

121
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,300
pretending to lose her memory.

122
00:05:36,860 --> 00:05:38,940
I'll send a man to test her.

123
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:42,140
Even if she really forgets everything,

124
00:05:43,060 --> 00:05:45,380
I'll make sure to create chaos for her,

125
00:05:45,380 --> 00:05:46,500
disturbing her life.

126
00:05:48,780 --> 00:05:50,540
You claim to be the real Cui Jiu?

127
00:05:50,940 --> 00:05:51,860
Do you have it?

128
00:05:52,700 --> 00:05:54,780
If you can produce it today, that's fine.

129
00:05:54,780 --> 00:05:56,020
If you can't,

130
00:05:56,380 --> 00:05:58,180
I'll accuse you of stealing my wife.

131
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:02,180
Compared to a piece of paper,

132
00:06:02,660 --> 00:06:04,340
I trust my eyes more.

133
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,020
I only recognize you as my husband.

134
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:14,380
His identity in the capital is fake.

135
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:16,460
A document cannot be true.

136
00:06:17,260 --> 00:06:18,460
Let's go to the authorities

137
00:06:18,620 --> 00:06:20,100
and expose his lies.

138
00:06:20,460 --> 00:06:21,740
True gold fears no fire.

139
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:23,060
We are a real couple.

140
00:06:23,060 --> 00:06:23,900
What's there to fear?

141
00:06:24,420 --> 00:06:25,460
The authorities, huh?

142
00:06:25,580 --> 00:06:26,420
Let's go.

143
00:06:26,460 --> 00:06:27,980
I'll let the authorities judge.

144
00:06:27,980 --> 00:06:29,260
- Move.
- Honey, let's go.

145
00:06:29,580 --> 00:06:31,300
Take a look.

146
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:32,540
Under the bright sun,

147
00:06:32,540 --> 00:06:34,060
he stole my wife from me.

148
00:06:59,100 --> 00:06:59,940
You...

149
00:07:09,780 --> 00:07:11,700
You sneaked up on me.

150
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:29,420
Where are they?

151
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:33,860
You prepared such a big show.

152
00:07:34,660 --> 00:07:36,340
Why not watch it all before leaving?

153
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:41,700
Who are you?

154
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:47,780
I've seen you before.

155
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:54,140
Miantang, why are you here?

156
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:56,580
If I weren't here,

157
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:58,700
how would I know who's behind this?

158
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:02,340
What are you talking about, Miantang?

159
00:08:02,660 --> 00:08:04,140
I just happened to pass by.

160
00:08:04,820 --> 00:08:06,900
Just happened to have tea at that stall

161
00:08:07,380 --> 00:08:09,100
and just happened to follow along.

162
00:08:09,980 --> 00:08:11,940
So many coincidences.

163
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:16,820
What's your background?

164
00:08:17,460 --> 00:08:19,180
Why incite that fake Cui Jiu

165
00:08:19,180 --> 00:08:20,260
to ruin my reputation?

166
00:08:21,580 --> 00:08:22,780
Incite?

167
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:25,580
The man just now was shouting and claiming

168
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:26,820
to be your husband.

169
00:08:27,580 --> 00:08:29,180
It's clearly a personal grudge.

170
00:08:29,580 --> 00:08:30,860
What does it have to do with me?

171
00:08:36,260 --> 00:08:37,660
The villagers watching near my shop

172
00:08:37,660 --> 00:08:39,020
couldn't figure out anything.

173
00:08:39,340 --> 00:08:41,140
They whispered and asked about the reason.

174
00:08:41,420 --> 00:08:42,940
You were just at that tea stall.

175
00:08:43,380 --> 00:08:44,260
How would you know

176
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:45,180
what he said?

177
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:50,460
Are you all fools?

178
00:08:58,460 --> 00:09:01,700
You'll have to blame yourselves

179
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:02,820
for walking right into it.

180
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:05,450
Move.

181
00:09:25,940 --> 00:09:26,780
Want to run away?

182
00:09:30,660 --> 00:09:31,500
Miss!

183
00:09:32,460 --> 00:09:33,300
Don't move.

184
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:34,940
Or I'll step on her.

185
00:09:35,140 --> 00:09:36,460
Still daring to fight me?

186
00:09:37,060 --> 00:09:38,180
Even though I'm weak,

187
00:09:38,180 --> 00:09:39,620
it's more than enough to hit you.

188
00:09:41,340 --> 00:09:42,460
Dear, you shouldn't fight.

189
00:09:42,460 --> 00:09:43,580
How can you do this?

190
00:10:01,940 --> 00:10:03,260
Who are you?

191
00:10:03,820 --> 00:10:04,700
Thanks

192
00:10:05,740 --> 00:10:06,900
to you all heroes

193
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:07,860
for your help.

194
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:08,940
Thank you, thank you.

195
00:10:11,420 --> 00:10:12,260
Heroes,

196
00:10:12,260 --> 00:10:13,220
thank you.

197
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:14,700
Here's some reward

198
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:15,820
from me and my husband.

199
00:10:15,820 --> 00:10:17,460
Please take it to buy drinks.

200
00:10:20,460 --> 00:10:21,300
Thank you, Madam.

201
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:23,700
I want to see

202
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:25,220
what she's really up to.

203
00:10:25,220 --> 00:10:26,060
Dear,

204
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:28,940
they have many people.

205
00:10:29,220 --> 00:10:30,300
They must be dangerous.

206
00:10:30,980 --> 00:10:32,940
Let's hand them over to the authorities.

207
00:10:33,380 --> 00:10:34,540
Please, heroes,

208
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:35,860
take these people

209
00:10:35,860 --> 00:10:36,740
to the authorities.

210
00:10:36,980 --> 00:10:37,860
Thank you, thank you.

211
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:52,620
The authorities will clear this up.

212
00:11:17,780 --> 00:11:19,260
Now you feel the pain?

213
00:11:25,260 --> 00:11:26,100
Is it better?

214
00:11:27,140 --> 00:11:28,340
Still hurting.

215
00:11:29,300 --> 00:11:30,700
What a useless miracle physician.

216
00:11:31,140 --> 00:11:33,100
He took so much effort to find the medicine

217
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:34,940
and it's useless.

218
00:11:35,620 --> 00:11:37,060
It was just applied.

219
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:38,700
Even Hua Tuo's medicine

220
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:40,100
wouldn't work this fast.

221
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:41,740
Bone injuries

222
00:11:41,740 --> 00:11:43,420
need time to heal.

223
00:11:43,420 --> 00:11:44,660
You know it needs time.

224
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:47,020
But you were so forceful earlier.

225
00:11:49,340 --> 00:11:50,500
I didn't know why.

226
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:53,140
When I saw that woman earlier,

227
00:11:53,780 --> 00:11:54,820
I felt

228
00:11:54,820 --> 00:11:56,300
an uncontrollable rage,

229
00:11:56,860 --> 00:11:58,780
wanting to tear her apart.

230
00:12:00,140 --> 00:12:01,140
I completely forgot

231
00:12:01,140 --> 00:12:03,060
about the injury on my hand.

232
00:12:04,220 --> 00:12:05,100
Do you know her?

233
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:08,980
I've only seen her once at the banquet

234
00:12:08,980 --> 00:12:09,980
with the neighbors.

235
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:12,660
That day, I just said

236
00:12:12,660 --> 00:12:13,500
I have a poor memory,

237
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:14,820
and she took it to heart,

238
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,620
sending someone to scheme against me.

239
00:12:18,140 --> 00:12:20,140
I really don't know what she's up to.

240
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:23,380
That rascal

241
00:12:23,740 --> 00:12:25,060
claimed to be Cui Jiu,

242
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:26,820
saying he's your husband.

243
00:12:26,820 --> 00:12:28,380
Forget about that dirty business.

244
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:30,980
That man's face is swollen

245
00:12:30,980 --> 00:12:32,140
with a lewd gaze.

246
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:33,660
He looks deceitful.

247
00:12:34,260 --> 00:12:35,420
Marrying him

248
00:12:35,420 --> 00:12:36,460
would be worse

249
00:12:36,460 --> 00:12:37,780
than being kidnapped by bandits.

250
00:12:47,820 --> 00:12:50,060
So according to you,

251
00:12:51,460 --> 00:12:52,860
if he were good-looking,

252
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:54,220
you'd just accept him?

253
00:12:54,220 --> 00:12:55,780
What are you saying?

254
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:57,460
I'm already married to you.

255
00:12:57,780 --> 00:12:58,980
A gentleman like you,

256
00:12:58,980 --> 00:13:00,580
cultured and talented,

257
00:13:00,580 --> 00:13:01,860
is exactly what I prefer.

258
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:03,780
Speaking of which,

259
00:13:04,180 --> 00:13:05,700
what was Yun'er thinking?

260
00:13:05,820 --> 00:13:06,740
How could someone

261
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:08,620
mistake their husband?

262
00:13:10,420 --> 00:13:11,860
I lost my memory,

263
00:13:11,860 --> 00:13:13,140
but I'm not a fool.

264
00:13:13,420 --> 00:13:15,220
Can't I tell if my spouse

265
00:13:15,220 --> 00:13:16,380
is sincere

266
00:13:16,380 --> 00:13:17,780
or has ulterior motives?

267
00:13:18,140 --> 00:13:18,980
Besides,

268
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:20,820
with my intelligence,

269
00:13:21,260 --> 00:13:22,940
how deep a scheme

270
00:13:22,940 --> 00:13:24,380
and how superb a skill

271
00:13:24,380 --> 00:13:26,260
would it take to impersonate

272
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:28,340
my husband so convincingly?

273
00:13:31,940 --> 00:13:33,420
Honey, what are you thinking?

274
00:13:36,260 --> 00:13:37,380
Nothing.

275
00:13:41,620 --> 00:13:42,780
I'm going to see what food

276
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:43,900
Nanny Li has prepared.

277
00:13:50,420 --> 00:13:54,620
(He Mansion)

278
00:14:00,580 --> 00:14:01,540
She's been ill for long.

279
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:02,660
Why isn't it getting better?

280
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:05,300
How humiliating.

281
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:06,220
If it were me,

282
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:07,460
I wouldn't dare to go out.

283
00:14:07,660 --> 00:14:09,900
She has high aspirations.

284
00:14:10,380 --> 00:14:11,660
Who would dare marry her now?

285
00:14:11,940 --> 00:14:14,140
Unless she finds another lord.

286
00:14:14,460 --> 00:14:15,620
Isn't that right?

287
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:21,220
Don't listen to their nonsense.

288
00:14:21,660 --> 00:14:22,500
Look here.

289
00:14:30,580 --> 00:14:31,420
Miss.

290
00:14:32,220 --> 00:14:34,540
Physician Zhao said
you can't go out these days,

291
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:35,780
